Keratosis pilaris otherwise known as chicken skin is extremely common: a dry skin condition caused by keratin (skin protein) accumulating in the hair follicles.

To manage:

👩🏿‍⚕️Start off with a salicylic acid cleanser to help combat the sebum that is trapping the keratin.

👩🏿‍⚕️Using glycolic acid helps to loosen the keratin plugs and reduce skin texture.

👩🏿‍⚕️ Topical retinoids are the magic ingredient that does everything in skincare and works wonders on keratosis pilaris.

👩🏿‍⚕️MOISTURISE - this is hugely important. Keratosis Pilaris causes very dry skin. Look out for ingredients like ceramides and urea!

