Here’s how to shop for ingrown hairs:

1. Use an exfoliating acid to cleanse, helps to free up the follicle.

2. Use ‘acne-fighting’ actives that also work really well on ingrown hairs such as benzoyl peroxide and retinols!

3. Use a light lotion

4. For infected ingrown hairs you can use hydrocortisone cream (and of course see your GP)

