I am not an authority on pots and pans, but, I do cook a lot and seem to have accumulated some favourites that I have now been using over and over for many years

A few things I consider

1. Use cookware only by reputable brands that abide by rules and regulations when it comes to the material used and that they test adequately to ensure continued safety with ongoing use. Because lets face it, I am not going to be testing each item I use for potentially toxic materials…
2. I regularly check my pots and pans for damage, if the coating looks damaged or it looks like its coming off, I no longer use it.
3. Only use the cookware as per manufacturer guideline, what I mean by this is, if the manual says, ‘do not put in oven’ or ‘do not heat without water or oil in the pan’ ‘or do not use metal spoons’ ‘or do not put in dishwasher’ I don’t do it. These are specific guidelines to ensure longevity and safety of the product.
4. Clean the cookware as per advice of the manufacturer, i.e if it says to use only soft (scourer free) cleaning with a sponge etc I stick to that. This probably means two things - no coating is shedding, and I’m preserving the life of the pan
5. Where possible I do try to use cast iron, and stainless steel. This in my opinion is the best way of avoiding any risk of any added chemicals (if that is your primary concern)

Let me know if you have any fav brands when it comes to cookware, I am sure we can benefit from this list :)

