One of the best ways I combat dehydrated skin over winter/harmattan is to use a thick, occlusive moisturiser. Here are some moisturisers I usually reach out for during the colder months. 

You’ll see that all of them contain ceramides. This was unintentional and purely coincidental. Ceramides are great for the cold weather because they hold skin cells firmly together. This locks moisture into the skin, preventing transepidermal water loss. Let’s dive in:

@Illiyoon Ceramide Ato Cream: alongside ceramides, this cream contains cholesterol and fatty acids. All three ingredients make up the main building blocks of our skin's barrier. In simple terms, this moisturiser will keep your skin healthy and happy. Texture wise, it is thick, weightless and reparative.

@cerave Moisturising Cream: my oily skin loves a rich, thick cream with a matte finish. Get this if you like the sound of that too. A little goes a long way. This also contains hyaluronic acid, glycerin and cholesterol, all of which support hydration and moisture retention.

@soonjung 2x Barrier Intensive Cream: this product is a great example of a lightweight cream that provides long-lasting protection. I was a little doubtful when I saw the soft texture but I was proven wrong. This contains nourishing ingredients like panthenol, shea butter and centella asiatica extract. A real winter fave.

@pyunkangyul Ato Cream: this is the thickest of the five moisturisers. Despite having a rich consistency, this cream quickly absorbs into the skin. It contains honey suckle extract, shea butter and peptides. If you’re looking for a heavy duty, non-greasy and nourishing cream, give this a try. 

@nichebeautylab Barrier Restoring Hydrating Cream (PR): this is another lightweight cream that offers long-lasting protection. It contains centella asiatica extract, hyaluronic acid and vitamins A, C and E. This personally performed well on its own. If you have dry skin, you can use a balm for some extra protection.

And that’s it! These moisturisers are suitable for every skin type. They are also calming and great for your skin-barrier.

