✨Thanks to Jacynth for this brilliant campaign. Please read! 

“An Open Letter to Beauty Brands,

We love that more of you are moving away & shifting focus from the outdated term ‘anti- aging’. We want to believe you are really committed to being a part of positive change, … 
but it’s somewhat undermined when you still use terms & promote narratives that mean the same as anti-aging, or carry anti-aging connotations. Because anti-aging isn’t just a singular, isolated term. It’s a culture & narrative. 

Any language that presents aging as a negative; that signs of it must be combatted; and/or that quintessence of beauty is youth - is still, in essence, anti-aging.

So even if the specific term is not there, replacing it with one that’s synonymous with it, isn’t the answer. Nor is using age-positive / pro age language in conjunction with anti-aging terminology. It is contradictory and comes across as inauthentic & performative.

We get it. Anti-aging is big business. And change takes time. But if you are truly with us in wanting to be a part of this amazing anti-ageism, age positive movement, then please understand it’s a commitment, not a gesture of tweaking a few words.

So this is our collective public request to stop using these terms which still mean ‘anti- ageing’. Why? Because language and words matters. We know you can do better, we WANT you to be a part of this movement, and we’re here to help.

Ageism Is Never In Style & The Community

P.S this is just a start - We’re inviting our whole community to take part via ‘Add Yours’ in stories to add to the list!” 

