one thing for certain, two things for sure - that dark mark will reappear 🫠

Things I do to manage and keep it at bay: 

1) Focus on barrier support - there’s no point in tackling dark marks if you don’t try and calm inflammation or work on the issue causing it. (If you’re really stumped book a quick consultation for a skin analysis with a professional)
Btw don’t hyaluronic acid your barrier back to health look for additional supporting ingredients like ceramides, lipids, centella asiatica, panthenol, niacinamide 

2) Use a dedicated dark spot serum - having at least one serum dedicated to evening out the skin tone or fighting dark marks in your skincare arsenal is key 

Ideally one with multiple ingredients (alpha arbutin, kojic acid, azelaic acid, niacinamide, licorice root extract, thiamidol…etc)

A few I enjoy:
@madeforhue - Supra Fade
@eucerin_uk - Dual Serum
@skinbetteruk - Even Tone Correcting Serum
@naturiumskin - Alpha Arbutin

3) Gently Exfoliate (1-2 a week) - this helps speed up the removal of dead skin cells giving you that cute smooth canvas. The goal is to not overdo it and annihilate your barrier because you’ll move 89 steps backwards 🫠

@medik8 - Press and Glow
@alumiermd_int - Bright and Clear Solution
@sundayriley - Lactic acid

*I prefer pairing my serums with retinal but I appreciate that not everyone is ready to jump into that realm so exfoliating gently is just as great 

Retinoids I love:
@medik8 - Crystal Retinal
@sable.labs - Okra Serum

4) Use Sunscreen (Everyday) - I mean this needs no further words but irrespective of dark marks wear your sunscreen please 💓

*Bonus note: Treatments are phenomenal too, especially for stubborn deep marks 
Chemical peels and microneedling are my go to for keeping my tone even. 
The Perfect peel is where it’s at! (That’s actually the name of the peel)

