✨Fact: 
‘On average, women use 12 personal care products a day, exposing themselves to 168 chemical ingredients.’ EWG

✨Fact: 
Plastic packaging waste from the beauty industry reaches over 120 billion units of packaging annually. Climate change is inevitable if brands don’t reconsider their approaches and shift to ecological and sustainable standards. Zero Waste Week. 

✨Fact: 
Truly clean brands care about their:
- Ingredients - using the fewest, least harmful, most nourishing and still effective. 
- Packaging - recycling, going plastic-free or refillable. 
- Impact on the environment - using environmentally friendly, biodegradable ingredients that don’t pollute our oceans. 
And they take pride in creating the safest most effective products they can for us. 

There are brands , however, who are happy to pop the ‘clean’ label on just because they took out parabens, for example, but they can leave in many other ingredients which are cheap and potentially harmful. These include (still!) Parabens, Quats, Pegs, Petroleum, Fragrance and Talc. 

As you can see, I’m super passionate about this! I’m
also creating a free Clean Beauty Guide to show how to choose cleaner makeup and personal care. 

It’ll be available in the New Year, so If you’d like to receive this (I would love to share it!), follow and I’ll post about it, or you can ping me your email now and I’ll save it ready for the launch! (BTW - I promise never to sell or pass on your info ✨)

